00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:19.720 align:middle line:84%
of more mass and less energy,
more matter, less mind."

00:02:19.720 --> 00:02:22.200 align:middle line:84%
And so, people are saying,
what do you mean mind?

00:02:22.200 --> 00:02:24.120 align:middle line:84%
You were just
talking about energy.

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:27.220 align:middle line:84%
And so, I would love for you
to take off and just give us

00:02:27.220 --> 00:02:29.940 align:middle line:84%
a little primer on why this
is central to everything

00:02:29.940 --> 00:02:31.530 align:middle line:90%
else we do and you do.

00:02:31.530 --> 00:02:32.380 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Sure.

00:02:32.380 --> 00:02:35.760 align:middle line:10%
I mean, living in survival
is living in stress.

00:02:35.760 --> 00:02:38.830 align:middle line:10%
And stress is when your body
is knocked out of homeostasis.

00:02:38.830 --> 00:02:41.420 align:middle line:10%
Stress is when your body
is knocked out of balance.

00:02:41.420 --> 00:02:43.810 align:middle line:10%
The stress response is
what our body naturally

00:02:43.810 --> 00:02:45.814 align:middle line:10%
does to return
itself back to order.

00:02:45.814 --> 00:02:47.480 align:middle line:84%
And we have different
types of stresses.

00:02:47.480 --> 00:02:49.680 align:middle line:84%
We have physical
stresses like accidents

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:52.240 align:middle line:90%
or injuries or traumas or falls.

00:02:52.240 --> 00:02:56.180 align:middle line:84%
We have chemical stresses
like viruses and bacteria

00:02:56.180 --> 00:03:00.570 align:middle line:84%
and hangovers and blood sugar
levels and hormones in foods.

00:03:00.570 --> 00:03:03.560 align:middle line:84%
And we have emotional stresses
like traffic jams and internet

00:03:03.560 --> 00:03:06.250 align:middle line:84%
connections and second
mortgages and single parenting

00:03:06.250 --> 00:03:07.610 align:middle line:90%
and 401(k)s.

00:03:07.610 --> 00:03:10.300 align:middle line:84%
In every one of those
things-- physical, chemical,

00:03:10.300 --> 00:03:13.240 align:middle line:84%
or emotional-- the body
responds by turning

00:03:13.240 --> 00:03:14.961 align:middle line:90%
on a primitive nervous system.

00:03:14.961 --> 00:03:16.335 align:middle line:84%
And that primitive
nervous system

00:03:16.335 --> 00:03:18.500 align:middle line:84%
is called the "fight or
flight" nervous system.

00:03:18.500 --> 00:03:20.400 align:middle line:84%
And when we are
experiencing a threat

00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:24.110 align:middle line:84%
in our external environment,
we mobilize an enormous amount

00:03:24.110 --> 00:03:28.360 align:middle line:84%
of energy to protect the body
in its external environment.

00:03:28.360 --> 00:03:33.590 align:middle line:84%
Now, those hormones of
stress, those chemicals,

00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:35.850 align:middle line:90%
produce a rush of energy.

00:03:35.850 --> 00:03:38.860 align:middle line:84%
And that rush of
energy wakes us up

00:03:38.860 --> 00:03:41.720 align:middle line:84%
to be more present
with three things.

00:03:41.720 --> 00:03:44.130 align:middle line:90%
We become focused on our bodies.

00:03:44.130 --> 00:03:46.260 align:middle line:84%
We become focused
on the environment.

00:03:46.260 --> 00:03:48.310 align:middle line:90%
And we become focused on time.

00:03:48.310 --> 00:03:52.490 align:middle line:84%
Now, all organisms in nature
can handle short-term stress.

00:03:52.490 --> 00:03:55.680 align:middle line:84%
A zebra gets chased
by a lion, 15 minutes

00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:59.440 align:middle line:84%
goes back to grazing, and the
body returns back to balance.

00:03:59.440 --> 00:04:01.830 align:middle line:84%
But human beings are
a little different.

00:04:01.830 --> 00:04:03.690 align:middle line:84%
When we turn on the
stress response,

00:04:03.690 --> 00:04:06.140 align:middle line:84%
we can turn it on
by thought alone.

00:04:06.140 --> 00:04:09.020 align:middle line:84%
We can begin to think
about some future event.

00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:12.710 align:middle line:84%
We can begin to anticipate
some worst-case scenario.

00:04:12.710 --> 00:04:16.290 align:middle line:84%
We can begin to expect something
to happen in our future

00:04:16.290 --> 00:04:17.910 align:middle line:90%
based on our past.

00:04:17.910 --> 00:04:20.180 align:middle line:84%
And we make thought more
real than anything else.

00:04:20.180 --> 00:04:23.010 align:middle line:84%
And the body
physiologically changes

00:04:23.010 --> 00:04:25.120 align:middle line:84%
as if that future
event is happening.

00:04:25.120 --> 00:04:27.790 align:middle line:84%
And we experience the
stress of that future event.

00:04:27.790 --> 00:04:31.490 align:middle line:84%
By the same means, we can unfold
the past bitter memory that's

00:04:31.490 --> 00:04:34.090 align:middle line:84%
tattooed in the recesses
of our gray matter

00:04:34.090 --> 00:04:35.650 align:middle line:84%
and, like magic,
it comes to life.

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:37.180 align:middle line:90%
And in that moment, it's real.

00:04:37.180 --> 00:04:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And the body as the
unconscious mind

00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:42.820 align:middle line:84%
does not know the difference
between the actual experience

00:04:42.820 --> 00:04:45.150 align:middle line:84%
that produces the
emotions and the emotions

00:04:45.150 --> 00:04:47.120 align:middle line:84%
that we fabricate
by thought alone.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:50.867 align:middle line:84%
So the hormones of
stress, then, then

00:04:50.867 --> 00:04:54.080 align:middle line:84%
begin to push the genetic
buttons that create disease.

00:04:54.080 --> 00:04:55.590 align:middle line:90%
It's a scientific fact.

00:04:55.590 --> 00:04:59.700 align:middle line:84%
And no organism in nature is
designed for long-term stress.

00:04:59.700 --> 00:05:02.630 align:middle line:84%
So when you and I are living
under the gun of the fight

00:05:02.630 --> 00:05:05.940 align:middle line:84%
or flight nervous system, we're
mobilizing all of this energy.

00:05:05.940 --> 00:05:09.210 align:middle line:84%
The rush of energy
becomes highly addictive.

00:05:09.210 --> 00:05:10.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:05:10.160 --> 00:05:13.830 align:middle line:84%
This becomes almost an
across the board type

00:05:13.830 --> 00:05:16.410 align:middle line:84%
of reaction on the whole
spectrum of emotions

00:05:16.410 --> 00:05:17.940 align:middle line:84%
from positive to
negative, right?

00:05:17.940 --> 00:05:18.690 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Right.

00:05:18.690 --> 00:05:21.400 align:middle line:84%
But the survival
emotions give the body

00:05:21.400 --> 00:05:24.060 align:middle line:84%
that rush of energy like
a triple cappuccino.

00:05:24.060 --> 00:05:28.490 align:middle line:84%
And we begin to subconsciously
or unconsciously associate

00:05:28.490 --> 00:05:31.420 align:middle line:84%
the problems and the
conditions in our life

00:05:31.420 --> 00:05:34.590 align:middle line:84%
to reaffirm our emotional
addiction so that we

00:05:34.590 --> 00:05:37.050 align:middle line:84%
can remember who we think
we are as a somebody.

00:05:37.050 --> 00:05:39.520 align:middle line:84%
So we keep the problems
and the circumstances

00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:41.570 align:middle line:84%
in our life to
reaffirm how we want

00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:43.570 align:middle line:90%
to feel based on that emotion.

00:05:43.570 --> 00:05:48.160 align:middle line:84%
Now, the emotions of anger,
of hatred, of aggression,

00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:52.870 align:middle line:84%
of competition, of control,
of fear, of anxiety, of guilt,

00:05:52.870 --> 00:05:55.216 align:middle line:84%
of shame, of insecurity,
of unworthiness,

00:05:55.216 --> 00:06:02.990 align:middle line:84%
of fear-- all of those
emotions, those emotions

00:06:02.990 --> 00:06:05.700 align:middle line:84%
are the emotions driven
by the hormones of stress.

00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:10.130 align:middle line:84%
And those emotions, then, cause
the ego to become selfish.

00:06:10.130 --> 00:06:14.350 align:middle line:84%
We become self-indulgent,
self-centered, self-serving,

00:06:14.350 --> 00:06:15.360 align:middle line:90%
self-aggrandizing.

00:06:15.360 --> 00:06:17.200 align:middle line:90%
It's all about the self.

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:20.830 align:middle line:84%
Now, when the zebra is
being chased by the lion,

00:06:20.830 --> 00:06:23.610 align:middle line:84%
she's only concerned
about three things.

00:06:23.610 --> 00:06:25.290 align:middle line:90%
I got to take care of this body.

00:06:25.290 --> 00:06:27.270 align:middle line:84%
Where in my environment
am I going to run?

00:06:27.270 --> 00:06:29.590 align:middle line:84%
And how much time do
I have to get there?

00:06:29.590 --> 00:06:32.120 align:middle line:84%
So the body, the
environment, and time.

00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:35.800 align:middle line:84%
And when you and I live
by those lower emotions

00:06:35.800 --> 00:06:41.310 align:middle line:84%
that I just talked about, we
begin to identify ourselves

00:06:41.310 --> 00:06:44.677 align:middle line:84%
as a body in this
environment and time.

00:06:44.677 --> 00:06:46.260 align:middle line:84%
We're concerned about
our bodies, what

00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:47.907 align:middle line:84%
we look like, what
our faces look like,

00:06:47.907 --> 00:06:49.990 align:middle line:84%
our wardrobe, the things
that we have in our life,

00:06:49.990 --> 00:06:52.000 align:middle line:84%
the things we don't
own, our problems.

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:53.270 align:middle line:90%
We obsess about time.

00:06:53.270 --> 00:06:55.820 align:middle line:84%
We become over focused
on these things.

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:58.800 align:middle line:84%
And in a sense, when those
hormones of stress are running,

00:06:58.800 --> 00:07:00.530 align:middle line:90%
we become materialists.

00:07:00.530 --> 00:07:04.100 align:middle line:84%
We begin to try to define
reality through our senses.

00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:08.650 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is where we become
more matter and less energy,

00:07:08.650 --> 00:07:10.300 align:middle line:90%
because we become materialists.

00:07:10.300 --> 00:07:15.990 align:middle line:84%
And if the atom is 99.99999%
energy and possibility,

00:07:15.990 --> 00:07:20.500 align:middle line:84%
we're focusing on the particle,
the 0.00001% of reality.

00:07:20.500 --> 00:07:23.044 align:middle line:84%
And we're missing out
on a lot of potentials.

00:07:23.044 --> 00:07:25.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so let's talk
about how you correlate, then,

00:07:25.460 --> 00:07:26.650 align:middle line:90%
energy to mind.

00:07:26.650 --> 00:07:28.650 align:middle line:84%
Because that whole
paragraph spoke

00:07:28.650 --> 00:07:29.890 align:middle line:90%
of energy, energy, energy.

00:07:29.890 --> 00:07:31.850 align:middle line:84%
Now you say, more
matter, less mind.

00:07:31.850 --> 00:07:32.930 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Mm-hmm.

00:07:32.930 --> 00:07:36.110 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you think about
it, quantum physics

00:07:36.110 --> 00:07:39.290 align:middle line:84%
says that your
subjective mind has

00:07:39.290 --> 00:07:41.610 align:middle line:84%
an effect on the
objective world,

00:07:41.610 --> 00:07:44.820 align:middle line:84%
that mind and matter are
co-related, their co-mingled.

00:07:44.820 --> 00:07:48.920 align:middle line:84%
But if you're trying
to change your life

00:07:48.920 --> 00:07:51.900 align:middle line:84%
by the emotions of
survival, your functioning

00:07:51.900 --> 00:07:56.872 align:middle line:84%
is more matter and less mind, so
you have no control or dominion

00:07:56.872 --> 00:07:58.580 align:middle line:84%
over anything in your
life because you're

00:07:58.580 --> 00:07:59.935 align:middle line:84%
vibrating at the
same frequency--

00:07:59.935 --> 00:08:00.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very low frequency.

00:08:00.600 --> 00:08:01.599 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: --as matter.

00:08:01.599 --> 00:08:03.850 align:middle line:84%
So you exert very little
influence on the outcome.

00:08:03.850 --> 00:08:07.565 align:middle line:84%
So now, when you and I are
in the creative state, when

00:08:07.565 --> 00:08:09.430 align:middle line:84%
you and I are truly
focused on creating,

00:08:09.430 --> 00:08:11.112 align:middle line:90%
this amazing thing happens.

00:08:11.112 --> 00:08:12.195 align:middle line:90%
We forget about ourselves.

00:08:12.195 --> 00:08:12.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:08:12.960 --> 00:08:16.270 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: We become
nobody, no thing, no time.

00:08:16.270 --> 00:08:17.710 align:middle line:90%
We become pure consciousness.

00:08:17.710 --> 00:08:19.350 align:middle line:90%
We become pure mind.

00:08:19.350 --> 00:08:21.560 align:middle line:84%
And that's the moment
we walk through the door

00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:22.810 align:middle line:90%
to the quantum field.

00:08:22.810 --> 00:08:25.660 align:middle line:84%
We no longer are
focusing on the particle.

00:08:25.660 --> 00:08:27.940 align:middle line:84%
Now we're focusing
on possibility.

00:08:27.940 --> 00:08:31.320 align:middle line:84%
And when an observer takes its
attention off the particle,

00:08:31.320 --> 00:08:34.200 align:middle line:84%
it turns into energy
and information.

00:08:34.200 --> 00:08:36.520 align:middle line:84%
So if you and I are
observing our life

00:08:36.520 --> 00:08:39.659 align:middle line:84%
from the same level of
mind every single day,

00:08:39.659 --> 00:08:42.559 align:middle line:84%
we keep infinite
patterns of information

00:08:42.559 --> 00:08:45.710 align:middle line:84%
collapsed into the same
reality called our life.

00:08:45.710 --> 00:08:49.780 align:middle line:84%
So then, in order for you to
change something on your body,

00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:51.900 align:middle line:84%
change something in
your environment,

00:08:51.900 --> 00:08:56.750 align:middle line:84%
or change some future time, you
have to forget about your body.

00:08:56.750 --> 00:08:58.580 align:middle line:84%
You have to forget
about your environment.

00:08:58.580 --> 00:08:59.830 align:middle line:90%
You have to forget about time.

00:08:59.830 --> 00:09:02.390 align:middle line:90%
You have to become selfless.

00:09:02.390 --> 00:09:04.760 align:middle line:84%
So going from
selfish to selfless

00:09:04.760 --> 00:09:08.770 align:middle line:84%
means we have to lay down
the very thing we used

00:09:08.770 --> 00:09:11.640 align:middle line:84%
our whole life to get
what we want for something

00:09:11.640 --> 00:09:12.530 align:middle line:90%
greater to happen.

00:09:12.530 --> 00:09:16.430 align:middle line:84%
And that requires, then,
dissociating and disconnecting

00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:18.320 align:middle line:84%
from our environment,
our body, and time.

00:09:18.320 --> 00:09:20.640 align:middle line:84%
And it requires, then,
taking our attention

00:09:20.640 --> 00:09:24.180 align:middle line:84%
off the emotions that
reaffirm the addiction that

00:09:24.180 --> 00:09:25.580 align:middle line:90%
keeps us human.

00:09:25.580 --> 00:09:26.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Indeed.

00:09:26.820 --> 00:09:27.810 align:middle line:90%
So beautifully put.

00:09:27.810 --> 00:09:30.460 align:middle line:84%
And I see these patterns
with some people

00:09:30.460 --> 00:09:36.020 align:middle line:84%
I know quite well, where there
is, maybe, one element of life

00:09:36.020 --> 00:09:37.580 align:middle line:90%
that is not certain.

00:09:37.580 --> 00:09:41.220 align:middle line:84%
And so, they'll go into a
survival mode that becomes

00:09:41.220 --> 00:09:45.160 align:middle line:84%
this... it's a
loop-- good people.

00:09:45.160 --> 00:09:47.470 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't allow them
to take their eye

00:09:47.470 --> 00:09:51.530 align:middle line:84%
off the ball of their own
reality, to become selfless.

00:09:51.530 --> 00:09:53.449 align:middle line:84%
And it becomes very
self-obsessive.

00:09:53.449 --> 00:09:55.490 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, the
peopel who-- you can always

00:09:55.490 --> 00:09:58.649 align:middle line:84%
tell a person who is
struggling with those emotions,

00:09:58.649 --> 00:10:00.440 align:middle line:84%
because they'll only
talk about themselves.

00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:02.110 align:middle line:90%
It's never about you.

00:10:02.110 --> 00:10:04.450 align:middle line:84%
They can't think greater
than how they feel.

00:10:04.450 --> 00:10:07.250 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, feelings
become the means of thinking.

00:10:07.250 --> 00:10:09.050 align:middle line:84%
And what they don't
know that they're doing

00:10:09.050 --> 00:10:13.560 align:middle line:84%
is they're creating a thought
that produces an emotion that's

00:10:13.560 --> 00:10:16.700 align:middle line:84%
addictive that causes them to
think equal to how they feel.

00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:18.540 align:middle line:84%
And they create
a state of being.

00:10:18.540 --> 00:10:22.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, it's a scientific fact
that the chemicals of stress

00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:26.430 align:middle line:84%
disregulate and down-regulate
genes and create disease.

00:10:26.430 --> 00:10:30.130 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you know that we can
turn on the stress response

00:10:30.130 --> 00:10:33.170 align:middle line:84%
just by thought alone, it
means, then, our thoughts

00:10:33.170 --> 00:10:34.540 align:middle line:90%
can make us sick.

00:10:34.540 --> 00:10:37.440 align:middle line:84%
So the question is if our
thoughts can make us sick,

00:10:37.440 --> 00:10:39.110 align:middle line:90%
can our thoughts make us well?

00:10:39.110 --> 00:10:42.080 align:middle line:84%
Because according to the
quantum model of reality,

00:10:42.080 --> 00:10:45.370 align:middle line:84%
all disease is a
lowering of frequency.

00:10:45.370 --> 00:10:47.810 align:middle line:84%
When you begin to
elevate your frequency,

00:10:47.810 --> 00:10:51.490 align:middle line:84%
your body becomes more
energy and less matter,

00:10:51.490 --> 00:10:53.840 align:middle line:84%
you become more wave
and less particle.

00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:57.400 align:middle line:84%
And you excite photons
into this state

00:10:57.400 --> 00:11:00.460 align:middle line:84%
where you begin to
broadcast new information.

00:11:00.460 --> 00:11:03.400 align:middle line:84%
So I think that
most people, then,

00:11:03.400 --> 00:11:05.390 align:middle line:84%
they try to create a
new personal reality

00:11:05.390 --> 00:11:06.672 align:middle line:90%
as the same personality.

00:11:06.672 --> 00:11:07.760 align:middle line:90%
And you can't do it.

00:11:07.760 --> 00:11:08.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You can't do it.

00:11:08.330 --> 00:11:10.621 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: You literally
have to become somebody else.

00:11:10.621 --> 00:11:13.790 align:middle line:84%
So the new science of
neuroplasticity and epigenetics

00:11:13.790 --> 00:11:16.020 align:middle line:84%
says that we're not
hard-wired to be

00:11:16.020 --> 00:11:18.240 align:middle line:84%
a certain way the
rest of our lives.

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:20.490 align:middle line:84%
And we're not
doomed by our genes,

00:11:20.490 --> 00:11:22.267 align:middle line:90%
that we're marvels of change.

00:11:22.267 --> 00:11:24.350 align:middle line:84%
But if you're thinking the
same thoughts-- I mean,

00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:25.350 align:middle line:90%
think about this.

00:11:25.350 --> 00:11:29.650 align:middle line:84%
The average person thinks
about 60,000 to 70,000 thoughts

00:11:29.650 --> 00:11:31.400 align:middle line:90%
in one day.

00:11:31.400 --> 00:11:33.700 align:middle line:84%
Out of those 60,000
to 70,000 thoughts--

00:11:33.700 --> 00:11:36.240 align:middle line:84%
and 90% of them are the same
thoughts as the day before--

00:11:36.240 --> 00:11:36.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I know.

00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:38.999 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that just awful when you
think about the implications.

00:11:38.999 --> 00:11:40.760 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: So think about it.

00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:43.270 align:middle line:84%
Same thought leads
to the same choice.

00:11:43.270 --> 00:11:45.630 align:middle line:84%
Same choice creates
the same behavior.

00:11:45.630 --> 00:11:47.760 align:middle line:84%
Same behavior creates
the same experience.

00:11:47.760 --> 00:11:50.540 align:middle line:84%
The same experience
produces the same emotion.

00:11:50.540 --> 00:11:53.380 align:middle line:84%
And that same emotion
inspires the same thought.

00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:55.130 align:middle line:90%
And we call that a personality.

00:11:55.130 --> 00:11:58.070 align:middle line:84%
So by the time
we're 35 years old,

00:11:58.070 --> 00:12:02.320 align:middle line:84%
our biology becomes equal
to how we think, how we act,

00:12:02.320 --> 00:12:03.360 align:middle line:90%
and how we feel.

00:12:03.360 --> 00:12:05.850 align:middle line:84%
So we fire and wire the
same circuits in our brain.

00:12:05.850 --> 00:12:07.430 align:middle line:90%
They become hard-wired.

00:12:07.430 --> 00:12:09.300 align:middle line:90%
We execute the same behaviors.

00:12:09.300 --> 00:12:11.090 align:middle line:90%
We reaffirm those circuits.

00:12:11.090 --> 00:12:13.149 align:middle line:84%
Those behaviors create
the same experiences

00:12:13.149 --> 00:12:14.440 align:middle line:90%
that produce the same emotions.

00:12:14.440 --> 00:12:16.640 align:middle line:90%
And that becomes familiar to us.

00:12:16.640 --> 00:12:20.380 align:middle line:84%
So then, when a person has
to cross the river of change

00:12:20.380 --> 00:12:22.870 align:middle line:84%
from the old self to
the new self, the moment

00:12:22.870 --> 00:12:26.280 align:middle line:84%
they start making a change-- and
the hardest part about change

00:12:26.280 --> 00:12:28.470 align:middle line:84%
is not making the same
choice as you did the day

00:12:28.470 --> 00:12:30.110 align:middle line:84%
before-- all of a
sudden they don't

00:12:30.110 --> 00:12:31.600 align:middle line:90%
feel like themselves any longer.

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:32.780 align:middle line:90%
You know what they do?

00:12:32.780 --> 00:12:35.010 align:middle line:84%
They return back
to the same choice

00:12:35.010 --> 00:12:37.762 align:middle line:84%
so they can feel the same
way because, God forbid,

00:12:37.762 --> 00:12:38.970 align:middle line:90%
they don't know who they are.

00:12:38.970 --> 00:12:41.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what you say,
well that's just how I am.

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:44.360 align:middle line:84%
You start living the
"that's just how I am"

00:12:44.360 --> 00:12:46.350 align:middle line:84%
kind of life, which
for most people

00:12:46.350 --> 00:12:48.120 align:middle line:90%
is not good enough for them.

00:12:48.120 --> 00:12:50.990 align:middle line:84%
I mean, most people would
say, well, if I could,

00:12:50.990 --> 00:12:52.270 align:middle line:90%
I would change a few things.

00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:54.500 align:middle line:84%
Very few people I
know of have life

00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:56.724 align:middle line:84%
nailed exactly the way
they want to have it wired.

00:12:56.724 --> 00:12:58.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: But don't
you think, though,

00:12:58.390 --> 00:12:59.917 align:middle line:84%
that most people
wait for crisis--

00:12:59.917 --> 00:13:00.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:13:00.500 --> 00:13:02.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --or trauma
or disease or diagnosis?

00:13:02.070 --> 00:13:03.778 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Unfortunately,
that is the fate

00:13:03.778 --> 00:13:04.850 align:middle line:90%
of the human condition.

00:13:04.850 --> 00:13:07.550 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: We reach
our lowest denominator

00:13:07.550 --> 00:13:08.820 align:middle line:90%
to decide to change.

00:13:08.820 --> 00:13:10.650 align:middle line:90%
And my message is why wait?

00:13:10.650 --> 00:13:13.050 align:middle line:84%
You can learn and change in
a state of pain and suffering

00:13:13.050 --> 00:13:15.205 align:middle line:84%
or you can learn and change in
a state of joy and inspiration.

00:13:15.205 --> 00:13:16.440 align:middle line:90%
It's a choice, isn't it?

00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:18.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I could
not agree more.

00:13:18.010 --> 00:13:20.280 align:middle line:84%
And what you were talking
about a moment ago,

00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:22.110 align:middle line:84%
you were-- So what
I'm understanding

00:13:22.110 --> 00:13:24.620 align:middle line:84%
here is that we
are now body-bound.

00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:26.920 align:middle line:84%
When we're in this lower
survival-kind-of-thought,

00:13:26.920 --> 00:13:32.000 align:middle line:84%
self-centered, just as a
reaction to survival itself,

00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:35.010 align:middle line:84%
then we're also cutting
ourselves off from

00:13:35.010 --> 00:13:38.050 align:middle line:84%
the possibility of reaching
into any of the higher,

00:13:38.050 --> 00:13:39.810 align:middle line:90%
finer aspects of mind.

00:13:39.810 --> 00:13:44.250 align:middle line:84%
And there was a model that
I found very useful once

00:13:44.250 --> 00:13:47.495 align:middle line:84%
upon a time about the
nature of matter and us.

00:13:47.495 --> 00:13:49.360 align:middle line:10%
And it was that if
you were to look

00:13:49.360 --> 00:13:53.420 align:middle line:10%
at our solar system and
the sun and the planets

00:13:53.420 --> 00:13:59.130 align:middle line:10%
as an atomic function, you
would have as much space

00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:02.260 align:middle line:10%
in every atom of
the body as you see

00:14:02.260 --> 00:14:05.561 align:middle line:10%
within our solar system, the
distance between the planets

00:14:05.561 --> 00:14:06.060 align:middle line:10%
and the sun.

00:14:06.060 --> 00:14:06.768 align:middle line:10%
>>DISPENZA: Sure.

00:14:06.768 --> 00:14:09.060 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: How can we
be anything but mind?

00:14:09.060 --> 00:14:09.960 align:middle line:10%
But space?

00:14:09.960 --> 00:14:12.152 align:middle line:10%
I mean, this is just
an illusion, isn't it?

00:14:12.152 --> 00:14:12.860 align:middle line:10%
>>DISPENZA: Sure.

00:14:12.860 --> 00:14:14.151 align:middle line:10%
And you know, it's interesting.

00:14:14.151 --> 00:14:18.110 align:middle line:10%
Because I think that
we view our life

00:14:18.110 --> 00:14:20.876 align:middle line:10%
through the lens of the
past, that the brain is

00:14:20.876 --> 00:14:22.250 align:middle line:10%
a reflection of
everything you've

00:14:22.250 --> 00:14:23.380 align:middle line:10%
experienced in your life.

00:14:23.380 --> 00:14:26.100 align:middle line:84%
So the brain is an
artifact from your past.

00:14:26.100 --> 00:14:28.890 align:middle line:84%
And emotions and feelings
are the end product

00:14:28.890 --> 00:14:30.160 align:middle line:90%
of past experiences.

00:14:30.160 --> 00:14:34.520 align:middle line:84%
And so people live by certain
emotions that define them.

00:14:34.520 --> 00:14:37.270 align:middle line:84%
Whether its suffering or
victimization or aggression

00:14:37.270 --> 00:14:39.190 align:middle line:84%
or anger or
judgment, that's kind

00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:42.040 align:middle line:84%
of the state of being that
they've become accustomed to.

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:44.710 align:middle line:84%
So we could say, then,
the emotion, then,

00:14:44.710 --> 00:14:48.220 align:middle line:84%
becomes the lens that
they view reality through.

00:14:48.220 --> 00:14:50.930 align:middle line:84%
So then, if you're thinking
certain thoughts that

00:14:50.930 --> 00:14:52.980 align:middle line:84%
create certain feelings,
and those feelings

00:14:52.980 --> 00:14:56.170 align:middle line:84%
are driving the same
thoughts, then in a sense

00:14:56.170 --> 00:14:59.690 align:middle line:84%
you're conditioning your body
and mind to live in the past.

00:14:59.690 --> 00:15:03.320 align:middle line:84%
And you cannot create a
new future holding onto

00:15:03.320 --> 00:15:04.550 align:middle line:90%
the emotions of the past.

00:15:04.550 --> 00:15:08.090 align:middle line:84%
So this is where people
begin to look at themselves

00:15:08.090 --> 00:15:10.880 align:middle line:84%
for the first time and
say, are these thoughts

00:15:10.880 --> 00:15:12.230 align:middle line:90%
really serving me?

00:15:12.230 --> 00:15:15.450 align:middle line:84%
Are these behaviors and habits
that I'm demonstrating really

00:15:15.450 --> 00:15:16.660 align:middle line:90%
part of my future?

00:15:16.660 --> 00:15:20.500 align:middle line:84%
And are these emotions
affecting anybody else but me?

00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:21.070 align:middle line:90%
I'm pushing--

00:15:21.070 --> 00:15:21.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's your creation.

00:15:21.560 --> 00:15:23.280 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --my own
genetic buttons, you know?

00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:24.670 align:middle line:90%
So you can blame the person.

00:15:24.670 --> 00:15:26.900 align:middle line:84%
You can blame the
condition in your past.

00:15:26.900 --> 00:15:30.700 align:middle line:84%
But in the end, you still
have to transmute that emotion

00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:33.960 align:middle line:84%
into wisdom, because a memory
without the emotional charge

00:15:33.960 --> 00:15:34.850 align:middle line:90%
is called wisdom.

00:15:34.850 --> 00:15:36.570 align:middle line:84%
And that's the name
of the game here.

00:15:36.570 --> 00:15:41.060 align:middle line:84%
So forget about the event,
just look at the emotion

00:15:41.060 --> 00:15:42.660 align:middle line:90%
that you're living by.

00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:45.900 align:middle line:84%
And look to see if that
emotion is part of your future.

00:15:45.900 --> 00:15:49.110 align:middle line:84%
And if it isn't, then you
have the choice to leave it,

00:15:49.110 --> 00:15:52.100 align:middle line:84%
because a wealthy person,
an abundant person,

00:15:52.100 --> 00:15:53.875 align:middle line:84%
would never think
lacking thoughts.

00:15:53.875 --> 00:15:55.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You do have
the choice to leave it.

00:15:55.750 --> 00:15:57.541 align:middle line:84%
However, it's not as
though there might not

00:15:57.541 --> 00:15:59.170 align:middle line:90%
be a tad of resistance.

00:15:59.170 --> 00:16:02.550 align:middle line:84%
So can we talk about the
slave-master relationship

00:16:02.550 --> 00:16:03.900 align:middle line:90%
between the mind and the body?

00:16:03.900 --> 00:16:08.110 align:middle line:84%
Because we're talking
about some intelligences,

00:16:08.110 --> 00:16:10.570 align:middle line:84%
in and of themselves,
that also fight

00:16:10.570 --> 00:16:12.200 align:middle line:90%
to protect their own existence.

00:16:12.200 --> 00:16:13.330 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Sure.

00:16:13.330 --> 00:16:16.410 align:middle line:84%
So I think that,
you know, we were

00:16:16.410 --> 00:16:20.530 align:middle line:84%
talking about by the time we're
35 years old, 95% of who we are

00:16:20.530 --> 00:16:24.590 align:middle line:84%
is a set of memorized behaviors,
emotional reactions, beliefs,

00:16:24.590 --> 00:16:28.760 align:middle line:84%
perceptions, attitudes that run
just like a computer program.

00:16:28.760 --> 00:16:31.080 align:middle line:84%
You turn them on and
they run automatically.

00:16:31.080 --> 00:16:32.860 align:middle line:90%
So people get up in the morning.

00:16:32.860 --> 00:16:34.300 align:middle line:90%
They brush their teeth.

00:16:34.300 --> 00:16:35.170 align:middle line:90%
They take a shower.

00:16:35.170 --> 00:16:37.750 align:middle line:84%
They wash themselves in
the same routine way.

00:16:37.750 --> 00:16:38.924 align:middle line:90%
They drive to work.

00:16:38.924 --> 00:16:40.340 align:middle line:84%
They see the same
people that push

00:16:40.340 --> 00:16:41.485 align:middle line:90%
the same emotional buttons.

00:16:41.485 --> 00:16:42.860 align:middle line:84%
They do the same
things that they

00:16:42.860 --> 00:16:44.850 align:middle line:90%
memorized and can do so well.

00:16:44.850 --> 00:16:49.350 align:middle line:84%
For the most part, most people
are functioning unconsciously.

00:16:49.350 --> 00:16:53.610 align:middle line:84%
So now, if 95% of
who you are is that,

00:16:53.610 --> 00:16:56.520 align:middle line:84%
then you're using 5%
of your conscious mind

00:16:56.520 --> 00:16:59.190 align:middle line:84%
to go against the program
that's been memorized.

00:16:59.190 --> 00:17:03.520 align:middle line:84%
Now, a habit is when the
body becomes the mind.

00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:05.880 align:middle line:84%
So if you're thinking
certain thoughts

00:17:05.880 --> 00:17:08.359 align:middle line:84%
and those thoughts are
producing emotional reactions

00:17:08.359 --> 00:17:11.099 align:middle line:84%
and chemicals in your body,
and those chemicals drive

00:17:11.099 --> 00:17:13.960 align:middle line:84%
the same thoughts, and you
keep that loop going on and on,

00:17:13.960 --> 00:17:17.240 align:middle line:84%
you'll condition your body
to memorize, subconsciously,

00:17:17.240 --> 00:17:19.374 align:middle line:90%
lack, unworthiness, insecurity.

00:17:19.374 --> 00:17:22.500 align:middle line:84%
And it'll run without
your conscious mind.

00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:26.370 align:middle line:84%
So then, when you come time to
change and you begin to say,

00:17:26.370 --> 00:17:28.574 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to think
these thoughts any longer.

00:17:28.574 --> 00:17:29.740 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to be a victim.

00:17:29.740 --> 00:17:30.710 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to complain.

00:17:30.710 --> 00:17:31.820 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to make excuses.

00:17:31.820 --> 00:17:33.403 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to feel
sorry for myself.

00:17:33.403 --> 00:17:34.920 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to
judge anybody else,

00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:37.290 align:middle line:84%
and you're breaking
that chemical continuity

00:17:37.290 --> 00:17:39.500 align:middle line:84%
between the mind
and the body, well,

00:17:39.500 --> 00:17:43.830 align:middle line:84%
once the body becomes the mind,
the servant is the master.

00:17:43.830 --> 00:17:47.040 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, the body
begins to-- just like anything

00:17:47.040 --> 00:17:48.760 align:middle line:84%
that you've trained,
it's the animal.

00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:51.940 align:middle line:84%
It's going to begin to send
signals back to the brain.

00:17:51.940 --> 00:17:53.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to say
things like, why don't you

00:17:53.940 --> 00:17:57.240 align:middle line:84%
start tomorrow, any
other day but today.

00:17:57.240 --> 00:17:59.310 align:middle line:84%
Today's not a good
day to change.

00:17:59.310 --> 00:18:01.670 align:middle line:84%
You're too much
like your mother.

00:18:01.670 --> 00:18:03.754 align:middle line:84%
You've tried this in the
past, it didn't work.

00:18:03.754 --> 00:18:04.670 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong with you?

00:18:04.670 --> 00:18:06.800 align:middle line:90%
This doesn't feel right.

00:18:06.800 --> 00:18:10.550 align:middle line:84%
And the moment we respond to
that voice as if it's true,

00:18:10.550 --> 00:18:14.120 align:middle line:84%
we return back to the same self,
thinking the same thoughts,

00:18:14.120 --> 00:18:17.200 align:middle line:84%
performing the same actions,
and living by the same emotions.

00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:19.540 align:middle line:84%
But crossing that
river of change,

00:18:19.540 --> 00:18:22.520 align:middle line:84%
then, means when you
become conscious that it's

00:18:22.520 --> 00:18:26.190 align:middle line:84%
your body trying to be the mind,
and it's giving it its best

00:18:26.190 --> 00:18:28.390 align:middle line:84%
effort to cause
you to return back

00:18:28.390 --> 00:18:30.940 align:middle line:84%
to the way you've
programmed it to be.

00:18:30.940 --> 00:18:32.660 align:middle line:84%
When you step out
into the unknown

00:18:32.660 --> 00:18:36.780 align:middle line:84%
and it feels uncomfortable
and it feels unfamiliar,

00:18:36.780 --> 00:18:38.940 align:middle line:84%
this is the best
place to create from,

00:18:38.940 --> 00:18:41.960 align:middle line:84%
because now the best way
to predict your future

00:18:41.960 --> 00:18:44.060 align:middle line:84%
is to create it
from the unknown.

00:18:44.060 --> 00:18:46.110 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is where
a person begins

00:18:46.110 --> 00:18:48.900 align:middle line:84%
to think about who they
want to be in their future.

00:18:48.900 --> 00:18:51.562 align:middle line:84%
They begin to imagine
what behaviors

00:18:51.562 --> 00:18:52.770 align:middle line:90%
they're going to demonstrate.

00:18:52.770 --> 00:18:54.470 align:middle line:84%
They begin to fall
in love with how

