of these so-called structures
because information

00:37:08.760 --> 00:37:10.630 align:middle line:90%
is so readily available.

00:37:10.630 --> 00:37:13.190 align:middle line:84%
And so, because you
can research anything

00:37:13.190 --> 00:37:15.980 align:middle line:84%
now-- I used to have
to go to the library

00:37:15.980 --> 00:37:19.390 align:middle line:84%
and pull these massive books off
the shelf, and sit in a room,

00:37:19.390 --> 00:37:21.270 align:middle line:84%
and fumble through
all these pages.

00:37:21.270 --> 00:37:24.250 align:middle line:84%
And you could-- at
your very fingertips--

00:37:24.250 --> 00:37:25.850 align:middle line:90%
Look at the medical model.

00:37:25.850 --> 00:37:28.094 align:middle line:84%
25 years ago, you were
diagnosed with a condition,

00:37:28.094 --> 00:37:30.010 align:middle line:84%
the doctor told you you
needed this procedure,

00:37:30.010 --> 00:37:32.370 align:middle line:84%
you signed on the dotted
line, and it was over.

00:37:32.370 --> 00:37:33.450 align:middle line:90%
Fast forward to today.

00:37:33.450 --> 00:37:35.840 align:middle line:84%
The doctor tells you
you have a condition.

00:37:35.840 --> 00:37:37.770 align:middle line:84%
You go on the internet
for the next two days

00:37:37.770 --> 00:37:38.920 align:middle line:90%
and you research it better.

00:37:38.920 --> 00:37:42.029 align:middle line:84%
And you know more about that
condition than your doctor.

00:37:42.029 --> 00:37:44.570 align:middle line:84%
And you say to your doctor, I
want to try this new procedure.

00:37:44.570 --> 00:37:46.550 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor says, well, I
don't know anything about that.

00:37:46.550 --> 00:37:47.716 align:middle line:90%
Or that's not going to work.

00:37:47.716 --> 00:37:48.780 align:middle line:90%
And you say, really?

00:37:48.780 --> 00:37:50.510 align:middle line:90%
Time to find a new doctor.

00:37:50.510 --> 00:37:52.240 align:middle line:84%
Because people
are now wanting to

00:37:52.240 --> 00:37:55.240 align:middle line:84%
empower themselves
with information.

00:37:55.240 --> 00:37:58.690 align:middle line:84%
So, classic time in history
because the traditional models

00:37:58.690 --> 00:38:01.540 align:middle line:84%
that are based on
the past have nothing

00:38:01.540 --> 00:38:03.830 align:middle line:90%
to do with a new future.

00:38:03.830 --> 00:38:09.350 align:middle line:84%
And so, waking up to
this time, right now,

00:38:09.350 --> 00:38:11.870 align:middle line:84%
is really saying to
every individual,

00:38:11.870 --> 00:38:14.600 align:middle line:84%
if you want peace in the
world, you better not

00:38:14.600 --> 00:38:17.160 align:middle line:84%
be arguing with your
neighbor, because you

00:38:17.160 --> 00:38:19.670 align:middle line:84%
have to demonstrate peace
everywhere in your life.

00:38:19.670 --> 00:38:23.720 align:middle line:84%
If you have a problem
with war or the government

00:38:23.720 --> 00:38:25.910 align:middle line:90%
taking things, start giving.

00:38:25.910 --> 00:38:28.090 align:middle line:84%
You have to demonstrate
all of that.

00:38:28.090 --> 00:38:30.000 align:middle line:84%
And when you do, you
give people permission

00:38:30.000 --> 00:38:32.330 align:middle line:90%
to do the same in their lives.

00:38:32.330 --> 00:38:35.230 align:middle line:84%
So because of
globalization, there's

00:38:35.230 --> 00:38:38.590 align:middle line:84%
a collapse going on in a lot
of these social structures

00:38:38.590 --> 00:38:40.220 align:middle line:84%
and really giving
people permission

00:38:40.220 --> 00:38:41.430 align:middle line:90%
to step outside of them.

00:38:41.430 --> 00:38:44.190 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's a really
healthy time to be alive.

00:38:44.190 --> 00:38:46.290 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yes, and
it's fascinating.

00:38:46.290 --> 00:38:48.840 align:middle line:10%
I look at this, where
you have stuck scenarios

00:38:48.840 --> 00:38:50.320 align:middle line:10%
like the Hatfields and McCoys.

00:38:50.320 --> 00:38:52.900 align:middle line:10%
And another one that is very
controversial to even bring up,

00:38:52.900 --> 00:38:56.010 align:middle line:10%
which is the notion of what
happens in the Holocaust,

00:38:56.010 --> 00:38:59.310 align:middle line:10%
for example, where the
theme is "never forget."

00:38:59.310 --> 00:39:00.210 align:middle line:90%
What happens?

00:39:00.210 --> 00:39:04.640 align:middle line:84%
What kind of pain is perpetuated
if a group of people,

00:39:04.640 --> 00:39:07.710 align:middle line:84%
or a family, or an individual
has been through something

00:39:07.710 --> 00:39:10.170 align:middle line:84%
extraordinarily
traumatic and painful.

00:39:10.170 --> 00:39:12.930 align:middle line:84%
And yet, chooses to
commit to keeping

00:39:12.930 --> 00:39:17.270 align:middle line:84%
that very memory alive through
repetition, repeating stories,

00:39:17.270 --> 00:39:17.880 align:middle line:90%
and so forth?

00:39:17.880 --> 00:39:19.180 align:middle line:90%
What does that do?

00:39:19.180 --> 00:39:21.590 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
I'll speak about it

00:39:21.590 --> 00:39:23.270 align:middle line:84%
from a biological
standpoint, which

00:39:23.270 --> 00:39:27.310 align:middle line:84%
is the safest
scientific standpoint.

00:39:27.310 --> 00:39:30.800 align:middle line:10%
Memories are just thoughts
that stay in the brain.

00:39:30.800 --> 00:39:34.620 align:middle line:10%
And if you keep firing and
wiring the same circuits,

00:39:34.620 --> 00:39:37.140 align:middle line:10%
you begin to cause
long-term relationships.

00:39:37.140 --> 00:39:39.170 align:middle line:84%
Learning is making
new connections.

00:39:39.170 --> 00:39:41.450 align:middle line:90%
Remembering is maintaining them.

00:39:41.450 --> 00:39:44.570 align:middle line:84%
So then, if we keep
the same level of mind

00:39:44.570 --> 00:39:47.980 align:middle line:84%
going every single day,
then our brain literally

00:39:47.980 --> 00:39:49.510 align:middle line:84%
is keeping those
circuits in place.

00:39:49.510 --> 00:39:53.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's nothing wrong with
remembering the experience.

00:39:53.990 --> 00:39:56.260 align:middle line:84%
But if you can
remember the experience

00:39:56.260 --> 00:39:57.690 align:middle line:90%
without the emotional charge--

00:39:57.690 --> 00:39:59.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, see, now
that's the key, isn't it?

00:39:59.690 --> 00:40:01.856 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --then you are
free from the experience.

00:40:01.856 --> 00:40:03.992 align:middle line:90%
Look at Nelson Mandela.

00:40:03.992 --> 00:40:04.700 align:middle line:90%
One of my heroes.

00:40:04.700 --> 00:40:05.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: [COUGH]
Yes, perfect example.

00:40:05.850 --> 00:40:07.266 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And
why do I love him?

00:40:07.266 --> 00:40:09.670 align:middle line:90%
27 years in prison, OK?

00:40:09.670 --> 00:40:13.600 align:middle line:84%
First 10 years of
his life, he hated.

00:40:13.600 --> 00:40:14.890 align:middle line:90%
He was angry.

00:40:14.890 --> 00:40:17.812 align:middle line:84%
And he said to
himself every day,

00:40:17.812 --> 00:40:19.270 align:middle line:84%
I'm never going to
get out of here.

00:40:19.270 --> 00:40:20.820 align:middle line:84%
I'm never going to
get out of here.

00:40:20.820 --> 00:40:22.230 align:middle line:84%
He kept thinking it, I'm never
going to get out of here.

00:40:22.230 --> 00:40:24.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You can just feel
the poisonous chemicals

00:40:24.580 --> 00:40:26.175 align:middle line:90%
coming into the body and brain.

00:40:26.175 --> 00:40:27.800 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And he
did it for 10 years.

00:40:27.800 --> 00:40:28.975 align:middle line:90%
And finally, he paused.

00:40:28.975 --> 00:40:33.270 align:middle line:84%
And he said, what if I
could get out of here?

00:40:33.270 --> 00:40:35.270 align:middle line:90%
What if I could get out of here?

00:40:35.270 --> 00:40:37.920 align:middle line:84%
And he started thinking
the "what if" question.

00:40:37.920 --> 00:40:41.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, he was stepping
outside of his environment

00:40:41.970 --> 00:40:42.720 align:middle line:90%
and his culture.

00:40:42.720 --> 00:40:44.880 align:middle line:84%
And he was willing
to make a difference.

00:40:44.880 --> 00:40:47.160 align:middle line:84%
So he starts
thinking about, what

00:40:47.160 --> 00:40:48.520 align:middle line:90%
could I do to get out of here?

00:40:48.520 --> 00:40:49.970 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden, he
thinks, he gets this idea,

00:40:49.970 --> 00:40:52.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to start writing
letters to the United States.

00:40:52.490 --> 00:40:54.970 align:middle line:84%
So every week he wrote
letters and wrote more letters

00:40:54.970 --> 00:40:56.870 align:middle line:84%
on apartheid and,
finally, he started

00:40:56.870 --> 00:40:58.980 align:middle line:84%
gaining a lot of
political attention.

00:40:58.980 --> 00:41:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And then, he was standing
outside of his cell one day,

00:41:03.190 --> 00:41:06.420 align:middle line:84%
and he thought, who's
going to lead this nation?

00:41:06.420 --> 00:41:09.230 align:middle line:90%


00:41:09.230 --> 00:41:11.090 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the
next thought is,

00:41:11.090 --> 00:41:13.170 align:middle line:84%
I wonder if I could
lead this nation?

00:41:13.170 --> 00:41:15.170 align:middle line:90%
Now, here's the key point.

00:41:15.170 --> 00:41:19.220 align:middle line:84%
He said, what would I have
to change about myself

00:41:19.220 --> 00:41:21.090 align:middle line:90%
to be a leader of this nation?

00:41:21.090 --> 00:41:21.835 align:middle line:90%
Now this--

00:41:21.835 --> 00:41:24.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
a profound and--

00:41:24.080 --> 00:41:27.050 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --is where you've
got to leave bitterness behind.

00:41:27.050 --> 00:41:29.800 align:middle line:84%
You have to leave betrayal
and hatred behind.

00:41:29.800 --> 00:41:34.970 align:middle line:84%
You have to leave anger and
judgment, prejudice, holding

00:41:34.970 --> 00:41:38.670 align:middle line:84%
grudges-- In 27 years
in the crucible,

00:41:38.670 --> 00:41:41.490 align:middle line:84%
he took base metals,
those survival emotions,

00:41:41.490 --> 00:41:43.230 align:middle line:90%
and turned them into gold.

00:41:43.230 --> 00:41:46.890 align:middle line:84%
And because he transmuted
those emotions,

00:41:46.890 --> 00:41:50.350 align:middle line:84%
there isn't an ounce of
malice in that man's body.

00:41:50.350 --> 00:41:52.740 align:middle line:90%
He gets to lead a nation.

00:41:52.740 --> 00:41:55.650 align:middle line:84%
So then, we're defined
by our adversity.

00:41:55.650 --> 00:41:57.930 align:middle line:84%
And when we can
look at the emotion

00:41:57.930 --> 00:42:00.100 align:middle line:84%
and really realize
that that emotion is

00:42:00.100 --> 00:42:04.520 align:middle line:84%
the residue from the past,
then when we begin to say,

00:42:04.520 --> 00:42:07.370 align:middle line:84%
this emotion, then, and these
behaviors and these habits

00:42:07.370 --> 00:42:10.800 align:middle line:84%
and these attitudes don't
belong to the ideal self

00:42:10.800 --> 00:42:15.490 align:middle line:84%
in the future, and you begin
to observe them-- look,

00:42:15.490 --> 00:42:18.280 align:middle line:84%
this concept in neuroscience
called meta-cognition, the fact

00:42:18.280 --> 00:42:20.856 align:middle line:84%
that we can think about
what we're thinking about,

00:42:20.856 --> 00:42:21.980 align:middle line:90%
to notice how we're acting.

00:42:21.980 --> 00:42:22.615 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That self-recognition.

00:42:22.615 --> 00:42:25.010 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Yeah, we can pay
attention and become conscious

00:42:25.010 --> 00:42:26.218 align:middle line:90%
of our unconscious behaviors.

00:42:26.218 --> 00:42:28.020 align:middle line:84%
It means we can modify
our states of being

00:42:28.020 --> 00:42:29.170 align:middle line:90%
to do a better job in life.

00:42:29.170 --> 00:42:30.030 align:middle line:90%
That's how we learn.

00:42:30.030 --> 00:42:31.780 align:middle line:84%
It's because of the
size of the fore-brain

00:42:31.780 --> 00:42:32.770 align:middle line:90%
and the frontal lobes.

00:42:32.770 --> 00:42:37.340 align:middle line:84%
So the fact that you're
observing the self

00:42:37.340 --> 00:42:40.260 align:middle line:84%
means that you're no
longer the program.

00:42:40.260 --> 00:42:42.600 align:middle line:84%
But you're the consciousness
observing the program.

00:42:42.600 --> 00:42:45.740 align:middle line:84%
That's when you begin to
objectify the subjective self.

00:42:45.740 --> 00:42:48.400 align:middle line:84%
This is when you begin to
detach from the programs.

00:42:48.400 --> 00:42:50.880 align:middle line:84%
And that's the first
step to change.

00:42:50.880 --> 00:42:51.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Beautiful.

00:42:51.970 --> 00:42:54.120 align:middle line:84%
OK, I want to talk
about another area

00:42:54.120 --> 00:42:57.260 align:middle line:84%
that I think most people
in Western culture--

00:42:57.260 --> 00:42:59.230 align:middle line:84%
and probably globally--
now struggle with.

00:42:59.230 --> 00:43:03.230 align:middle line:84%
And that is, life has
been, so to speak, wired.

00:43:03.230 --> 00:43:05.300 align:middle line:84%
And part of it because
of survival issues,

00:43:05.300 --> 00:43:06.970 align:middle line:84%
basic day-to-day
stuff you talked

00:43:06.970 --> 00:43:08.990 align:middle line:84%
about in the first
minute of the show.

00:43:08.990 --> 00:43:12.500 align:middle line:84%
We are stuck in this high
beta or this beta state.

00:43:12.500 --> 00:43:15.390 align:middle line:84%
And basically, we're
just grinding, grinding,

00:43:15.390 --> 00:43:17.930 align:middle line:84%
grinding in this beta
state, which really

00:43:17.930 --> 00:43:22.100 align:middle line:84%
is the antithesis of going
into the flow of the other part

00:43:22.100 --> 00:43:23.430 align:middle line:90%
of their true mind.

00:43:23.430 --> 00:43:25.880 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: I'm so glad you
realize that, because this

00:43:25.880 --> 00:43:28.000 align:middle line:84%
is the paradigm where
people get stuck.

00:43:28.000 --> 00:43:30.980 align:middle line:84%
If you're analyzing your
life within the emotions

00:43:30.980 --> 00:43:34.270 align:middle line:84%
that you've memorized
based on survival,

00:43:34.270 --> 00:43:36.915 align:middle line:84%
you're firing and
wiring the circuits

00:43:36.915 --> 00:43:40.660 align:middle line:84%
and driving your brain into a
higher, more analytical state

00:43:40.660 --> 00:43:42.790 align:middle line:84%
and away from the
operating system where

00:43:42.790 --> 00:43:44.080 align:middle line:90%
true change takes place.

00:43:44.080 --> 00:43:44.597 align:middle line:90%
Now--

00:43:44.597 --> 00:43:46.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But we pride
ourselves in the West

00:43:46.430 --> 00:43:47.530 align:middle line:90%
on this high beta state.

00:43:47.530 --> 00:43:48.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Yeah,
and how's it working?

00:43:48.660 --> 00:43:49.015 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah!

00:43:49.015 --> 00:43:50.090 align:middle line:84%
It's not working
too well, is it?

00:43:50.090 --> 00:43:50.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: More pharmaceuticals--

00:43:50.730 --> 00:43:52.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Talk about
high beta, what

00:43:52.230 --> 00:43:54.220 align:middle line:84%
it is, what happens
chemically, and how

00:43:54.220 --> 00:43:55.520 align:middle line:90%
we end up in this space.

00:43:55.520 --> 00:43:58.160 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So, when we're
under the fight or flight

00:43:58.160 --> 00:44:02.020 align:middle line:84%
nervous system, we have to
get a super rush of energy.

00:44:02.020 --> 00:44:03.970 align:middle line:84%
And the brain has to
become super alert.

00:44:03.970 --> 00:44:05.600 align:middle line:84%
And we have to
become super vigilant

00:44:05.600 --> 00:44:07.100 align:middle line:90%
because there's an emergency.

00:44:07.100 --> 00:44:08.960 align:middle line:90%
We're now in high gear.

00:44:08.960 --> 00:44:10.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, you have three
levels of beta.

00:44:10.970 --> 00:44:12.230 align:middle line:90%
You have low-level beta.

00:44:12.230 --> 00:44:14.970 align:middle line:84%
Right now, you and I pretty
much are in low-level beta.

00:44:14.970 --> 00:44:16.790 align:middle line:84%
If I said to you,
listen, I'm going

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:18.320 align:middle line:84%
to test you on all
of this material.

00:44:18.320 --> 00:44:20.990 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't pass the
test, you can't leave tonight.

00:44:20.990 --> 00:44:23.390 align:middle line:84%
You may move into a
little mid-range beta.

00:44:23.390 --> 00:44:25.900 align:middle line:84%
Well, high-range beta
is, like, twice as high

00:44:25.900 --> 00:44:26.810 align:middle line:90%
as mid-range beta.

00:44:26.810 --> 00:44:29.450 align:middle line:84%
And that's when you're freaked
out, when you're scared,

00:44:29.450 --> 00:44:31.530 align:middle line:84%
when you're angry,
when you're frustrated.

00:44:31.530 --> 00:44:35.140 align:middle line:84%
And in high-range beta, it's
like driving your sports car

00:44:35.140 --> 00:44:36.790 align:middle line:90%
in first gear.

00:44:36.790 --> 00:44:38.840 align:middle line:84%
And the brain begins
to break down.

00:44:38.840 --> 00:44:42.390 align:middle line:84%
And the patterns that you
see on EEG readings become

00:44:42.390 --> 00:44:44.710 align:middle line:84%
very incoherent,
disorganized, disintegrated.

00:44:44.710 --> 00:44:47.042 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, in your
book, I love the graphs

00:44:47.042 --> 00:44:48.500 align:middle line:84%
you have on that,
very interesting.

00:44:48.500 --> 00:44:52.810 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So in high beta,
you believe that the outer world

00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:55.130 align:middle line:84%
is more real than
the inner world.

00:44:55.130 --> 00:44:59.240 align:middle line:84%
And in high beta, your
brain is running a loop,

00:44:59.240 --> 00:45:01.720 align:middle line:84%
and you're overly
analyzing your problems.

00:45:01.720 --> 00:45:05.940 align:middle line:84%
And the analysis is causing
the emotions to be reinforced.

00:45:05.940 --> 00:45:08.730 align:middle line:84%
And when you begin to
realize that in order

00:45:08.730 --> 00:45:10.320 align:middle line:84%
for you to change,
your brain has

00:45:10.320 --> 00:45:13.730 align:middle line:84%
to move from beta to
alpha-- and in alpha,

00:45:13.730 --> 00:45:17.290 align:middle line:84%
the inner world starts to become
more real than the outer world.

00:45:17.290 --> 00:45:20.120 align:middle line:84%
If you're addicted
to those emotions,

00:45:20.120 --> 00:45:22.785 align:middle line:84%
no new information can come
into the nervous system--

00:45:22.785 --> 00:45:23.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's like a wall.

00:45:23.910 --> 00:45:25.868 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --that is
not equal to the emotion.

00:45:25.868 --> 00:45:29.960 align:middle line:84%
And that's why, when
people get in this state,

00:45:29.960 --> 00:45:33.700 align:middle line:84%
they get lost, because
they can't hear it

00:45:33.700 --> 00:45:36.045 align:middle line:84%
because it's not
a time to learn.

00:45:36.045 --> 00:45:37.660 align:middle line:84%
It's not a time for
new information.

00:45:37.660 --> 00:45:39.830 align:middle line:84%
It's a time to
react and survive.

00:45:39.830 --> 00:45:41.840 align:middle line:84%
So when the emotions
get highly addictive

00:45:41.840 --> 00:45:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and the brain moves
in this pattern,

00:45:43.370 --> 00:45:45.300 align:middle line:84%
people are trying
to force the outcome

00:45:45.300 --> 00:45:47.080 align:middle line:84%
and use the ego to
change their life.

00:45:47.080 --> 00:45:51.160 align:middle line:84%
Now, moving into
meditative states

00:45:51.160 --> 00:45:52.800 align:middle line:84%
is moving into
those alpha states

00:45:52.800 --> 00:45:55.170 align:middle line:84%
where you begin to
eliminate the information

00:45:55.170 --> 00:45:56.950 align:middle line:90%
from the external environment.

00:45:56.950 --> 00:45:59.960 align:middle line:84%
When you begin to
slip back into alpha,

00:45:59.960 --> 00:46:02.940 align:middle line:84%
your thinking brain
quiets way down.

00:46:02.940 --> 00:46:04.835 align:middle line:84%
Now, people do
this all the time.

00:46:04.835 --> 00:46:05.960 align:middle line:90%
They don't know they do it.

00:46:05.960 --> 00:46:07.560 align:middle line:84%
When you're driving
down the road

00:46:07.560 --> 00:46:10.960 align:middle line:90%
in your car and all of sudden--

00:46:10.960 --> 00:46:12.627 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --somewhere
just above delta!

00:46:12.627 --> 00:46:14.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
you're trancing out.

00:46:14.210 --> 00:46:15.780 align:middle line:84%
And you're thinking
about something.

00:46:15.780 --> 00:46:17.090 align:middle line:84%
And you're not
aware of your body.

00:46:17.090 --> 00:46:19.190 align:middle line:84%
You don't see the road or
the environment of the--

00:46:19.190 --> 00:46:20.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You've
lost track of time.

00:46:20.000 --> 00:46:21.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: You've
lost track of time.

00:46:21.070 --> 00:46:22.710 align:middle line:84%
Your brain moves
from beta to alpha.

00:46:22.710 --> 00:46:24.560 align:middle line:84%
We could say that,
in that moment,

00:46:24.560 --> 00:46:26.870 align:middle line:84%
the inner world became more
real than the outer world,

00:46:26.870 --> 00:46:29.940 align:middle line:84%
the imaginary world became more
real than the external world.

00:46:29.940 --> 00:46:33.310 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you're in high
beta, that never happens.

00:46:33.310 --> 00:46:36.030 align:middle line:84%
Because the brain doesn't pause
enough to store information.

00:46:36.030 --> 00:46:37.905 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You know, it's
funny because you'll

00:46:37.905 --> 00:46:41.000 align:middle line:84%
see at conferences,
spiritual conferences,

00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:43.166 align:middle line:84%
you'll see different
kinds of personalities.

00:46:43.166 --> 00:46:44.790 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's there
for their own reason.

00:46:44.790 --> 00:46:48.450 align:middle line:84%
But I've always wondered
about individuals

00:46:48.450 --> 00:46:52.070 align:middle line:84%
when you see them just
taking notes, detailed notes,

00:46:52.070 --> 00:46:55.320 align:middle line:84%
and using the analytical
process so much.

00:46:55.320 --> 00:46:58.570 align:middle line:84%
I always wonder, is
anything actually coming in?

00:46:58.570 --> 00:47:00.950 align:middle line:84%
Now, maybe it's just a
process for some minds' need

00:47:00.950 --> 00:47:03.900 align:middle line:84%
to hold on and analyze and
record to maybe take it

00:47:03.900 --> 00:47:05.200 align:middle line:90%
in later on.

00:47:05.200 --> 00:47:08.735 align:middle line:84%
But it almost seems like
it's blocking the experience.

00:47:08.735 --> 00:47:11.662 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: You know, knowledge
is the precursor to experience.

00:47:11.662 --> 00:47:13.120 align:middle line:84%
The more knowledge
you have, you're

00:47:13.120 --> 00:47:14.670 align:middle line:84%
more prepared for
the experience.

00:47:14.670 --> 00:47:17.820 align:middle line:84%
And I think that when you go
to these conferences-- and this

00:47:17.820 --> 00:47:20.400 align:middle line:84%
is why I've kind of stopped
doing a lot of the conferences

00:47:20.400 --> 00:47:24.680 align:middle line:84%
and keynotes, because
it's philosophy.

00:47:24.680 --> 00:47:28.090 align:middle line:84%
Until you initiate
that philosophy,

00:47:28.090 --> 00:47:29.990 align:middle line:84%
until you initiate
it and practice it

00:47:29.990 --> 00:47:32.230 align:middle line:90%
does it become truth or wisdom.

00:47:32.230 --> 00:47:36.520 align:middle line:84%
So if people need to write that
stuff down and ideo-motorwise

00:47:36.520 --> 00:47:38.200 align:middle line:84%
create some circuits
in their brain,

00:47:38.200 --> 00:47:41.000 align:middle line:84%
and that's how they pay
attention, then go for it.

00:47:41.000 --> 00:47:43.590 align:middle line:84%
But don't sit there and
analyze the information.

00:47:43.590 --> 00:47:46.450 align:middle line:84%
Take the information and
ask this simple question:

00:47:46.450 --> 00:47:49.260 align:middle line:90%
how can I use this in my life?

00:47:49.260 --> 00:47:52.200 align:middle line:84%
Now, once you start
applying it, you just

00:47:52.200 --> 00:47:55.810 align:middle line:84%
went from the philosopher
to the initiate.

00:47:55.810 --> 00:47:58.000 align:middle line:84%
And if you can
reproduce an experience

00:47:58.000 --> 00:48:00.400 align:middle line:84%
based on the knowledge you
learn over and over again,

00:48:00.400 --> 00:48:03.690 align:middle line:84%
now you're beginning to
master that knowledge.

00:48:03.690 --> 00:48:08.620 align:middle line:84%
You go from knowing all
the way to knowingness.

00:48:08.620 --> 00:48:10.214 align:middle line:84%
You know to knowing
to knowingness.

00:48:10.214 --> 00:48:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And when you get to that
point of knowingness,

00:48:12.130 --> 00:48:15.990 align:middle line:84%
where you know that you
know, or you know how,

00:48:15.990 --> 00:48:17.492 align:middle line:84%
but you've done it
so many times you

00:48:17.492 --> 00:48:20.390 align:middle line:84%
don't even know how you know
how, it's now innate in you.

00:48:20.390 --> 00:48:21.100 align:middle line:90%
It's who you are.

00:48:21.100 --> 00:48:23.600 align:middle line:84%
And that's where we
need to go as a culture.

00:48:23.600 --> 00:48:25.680 align:middle line:84%
We need to, all
of a sudden, break

00:48:25.680 --> 00:48:28.270 align:middle line:84%
from these
philosophical arguments.

00:48:28.270 --> 00:48:30.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's why we're
doing the workshops,

00:48:30.940 --> 00:48:36.330 align:middle line:84%
because we're all about,
really-- it's a time in history

00:48:36.330 --> 00:48:38.540 align:middle line:90%
not just to learn information.

00:48:38.540 --> 00:48:40.500 align:middle line:84%
It's a time in history,
really, to learn

00:48:40.500 --> 00:48:41.880 align:middle line:90%
how to use that information.

00:48:41.880 --> 00:48:43.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:48:43.030 --> 00:48:46.000 align:middle line:84%
And yet at the same time,
going back the other direction

00:48:46.000 --> 00:48:49.080 align:middle line:84%
again-- because I'm just trying
to cover all the influences

00:48:49.080 --> 00:48:52.030 align:middle line:84%
that we're under so we can
recognize them and break that

00:48:52.030 --> 00:48:53.950 align:middle line:84%
spell-- the media
takes advantage

00:48:53.950 --> 00:48:56.740 align:middle line:84%
of these frantic,
survival-oriented, high beta

00:48:56.740 --> 00:49:00.406 align:middle line:84%
states of mind and
further reinforces them.

00:49:00.406 --> 00:49:02.340 align:middle line:84%
And you and I, in our
last conversation,

00:49:02.340 --> 00:49:04.140 align:middle line:90%
spoke a little bit about that.

00:49:04.140 --> 00:49:08.720 align:middle line:84%
But mostly we were talking
about the effects in that area

00:49:08.720 --> 00:49:11.962 align:middle line:84%
of what happens when
children start becoming --

00:49:11.962 --> 00:49:15.930 align:middle line:84%
I was going to say
addicted, that's not it--

00:49:15.930 --> 00:49:18.780 align:middle line:84%
entrained to video
games, for example.

00:49:18.780 --> 00:49:21.180 align:middle line:84%
Now, this gets into
ethical, moral things.

00:49:21.180 --> 00:49:25.020 align:middle line:84%
We get into, now, the drones and
the drone issue and the people

00:49:25.020 --> 00:49:26.190 align:middle line:90%
that operate them.

00:49:26.190 --> 00:49:28.510 align:middle line:84%
So in a short bit--
because then I

00:49:28.510 --> 00:49:31.730 align:middle line:84%
want to get into some of what
you do in your workshops--

00:49:31.730 --> 00:49:36.170 align:middle line:84%
how do we address this mass
kind of enslavement, entrainment

00:49:36.170 --> 00:49:37.840 align:middle line:90%
by media and video games?

00:49:37.840 --> 00:49:38.730 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Mmm.

00:49:38.730 --> 00:49:46.570 align:middle line:84%
If you took one hour of your day
and retreated from your life,

00:49:46.570 --> 00:49:51.950 align:middle line:84%
truly shut off your cell phone,
powered down the computer,

00:49:51.950 --> 00:49:53.375 align:middle line:84%
you got up at 5:00
in the morning

00:49:53.375 --> 00:49:56.520 align:middle line:84%
or whatever time is good
for you before your day,

00:49:56.520 --> 00:49:58.420 align:middle line:84%
when your brain is
already in alpha

00:49:58.420 --> 00:50:01.450 align:middle line:84%
and the brain chemistry
is just right to dream,

00:50:01.450 --> 00:50:05.070 align:middle line:84%
and you sat down
and you said, what

00:50:05.070 --> 00:50:07.690 align:middle line:84%
is the greatest ideal
of myself that I

00:50:07.690 --> 00:50:10.350 align:middle line:84%
want to present to
the world today?

00:50:10.350 --> 00:50:15.700 align:middle line:84%
And you sat there and you
changed your state of being,

00:50:15.700 --> 00:50:18.300 align:middle line:84%
you worked until you
were that person,

00:50:18.300 --> 00:50:21.530 align:middle line:84%
you would have to forget
about the people in your life,

00:50:21.530 --> 00:50:23.660 align:middle line:84%
the things that you
have to do, the things

00:50:23.660 --> 00:50:26.130 align:middle line:84%
you own, the places you have
to go at different times,

00:50:26.130 --> 00:50:28.530 align:middle line:84%
and all the experiences
in your life

00:50:28.530 --> 00:50:31.090 align:middle line:90%
that reaffirm your identity.

00:50:31.090 --> 00:50:35.770 align:middle line:84%
You would have to get beyond
yourself in that moment.

00:50:35.770 --> 00:50:40.140 align:middle line:84%
And when you become conscious
of your unconscious self,

00:50:40.140 --> 00:50:42.750 align:middle line:84%
you are less likely
to be controlled

00:50:42.750 --> 00:50:46.260 align:middle line:84%
because you are no longer
being manipulated emotionally.

00:50:46.260 --> 00:50:48.710 align:middle line:84%
So you can manipulate
people with fear.

00:50:48.710 --> 00:50:50.920 align:middle line:84%
You can manipulate
people with need.

00:50:50.920 --> 00:50:53.390 align:middle line:84%
You can manipulate
people with lack.

00:50:53.390 --> 00:50:55.880 align:middle line:84%
You can cause people
to consume because they

00:50:55.880 --> 00:50:57.910 align:middle line:90%
don't look a certain way.

00:50:57.910 --> 00:51:00.870 align:middle line:84%
And so this indoctrination
into this idea

00:51:00.870 --> 00:51:03.670 align:middle line:84%
that you can rely on
something outside of you

00:51:03.670 --> 00:51:06.300 align:middle line:84%
to make you feel
better is the exact way

00:51:06.300 --> 00:51:08.430 align:middle line:90%
you control a culture.

00:51:08.430 --> 00:51:11.910 align:middle line:84%
When you begin to transmute
those survival emotions

00:51:11.910 --> 00:51:16.310 align:middle line:84%
into elevated states, and
the joy and the love for life

00:51:16.310 --> 00:51:19.330 align:middle line:84%
is within you,
you're more awake.

00:51:19.330 --> 00:51:20.992 align:middle line:84%
And when everybody's
looking one way,

00:51:20.992 --> 00:51:22.200 align:middle line:90%
you're looking the other way.

00:51:22.200 --> 00:51:24.520 align:middle line:84%
And you're no longer
manipulated by fear.

00:51:24.520 --> 00:51:26.530 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I went to an
event in Santiago.

00:51:26.530 --> 00:51:28.570 align:middle line:84%
There was 1,000
people in my audience

00:51:28.570 --> 00:51:33.660 align:middle line:84%
and half the people were wearing
masks because of the avian flu.

00:51:33.660 --> 00:51:37.500 align:middle line:84%
And I just said, you cannot
believe that to be the truth.

00:51:37.500 --> 00:51:39.570 align:middle line:90%
It's just not that way.

00:51:39.570 --> 00:51:43.280 align:middle line:84%
So you produce something
in the marketplace

00:51:43.280 --> 00:51:45.320 align:middle line:84%
that creates a little
fear, that people

00:51:45.320 --> 00:51:46.890 align:middle line:90%
think they have free will.

00:51:46.890 --> 00:51:48.270 align:middle line:90%
They don't have free will.

00:51:48.270 --> 00:51:49.800 align:middle line:84%
You think, oh, I'm
going to choose

00:51:49.800 --> 00:51:52.035 align:middle line:90%
Bayer instead of Excedrin.

00:51:52.035 --> 00:51:52.910 align:middle line:90%
That's not free will.

00:51:52.910 --> 00:51:55.160 align:middle line:84%
That's making choices
based on knowns.

00:51:55.160 --> 00:51:57.690 align:middle line:10%
Free-willed
individuals, genius, is

00:51:57.690 --> 00:52:00.050 align:middle line:10%
someone who steps
outside of convention

00:52:00.050 --> 00:52:03.060 align:middle line:10%
and who's willing to stay
outside of convention

00:52:03.060 --> 00:52:04.730 align:middle line:10%
until they produce an effect.

00:52:04.730 --> 00:52:08.030 align:middle line:10%
And they go from being
foolhardy and insane to becoming

00:52:08.030 --> 00:52:09.580 align:middle line:10%
a mystic or a saint.

00:52:09.580 --> 00:52:11.930 align:middle line:10%
But there's enough
people in this world now

00:52:11.930 --> 00:52:13.720 align:middle line:10%
that are beginning
to wake up and see

00:52:13.720 --> 00:52:16.355 align:middle line:10%
through the deceit and the
greed and the competition

00:52:16.355 --> 00:52:18.820 align:middle line:10%
that that is not
the model that's

00:52:18.820 --> 00:52:22.310 align:middle line:10%
going to sustain a culture,
because no organisms in nature

00:52:22.310 --> 00:52:24.300 align:middle line:10%
survive in competition.

00:52:24.300 --> 00:52:27.300 align:middle line:10%
They survive when they cooperate
and they worked together.

00:52:27.300 --> 00:52:29.600 align:middle line:10%
It's a time, this is
a nodal point for us

00:52:29.600 --> 00:52:30.620 align:middle line:10%
to begin to wake up.

00:52:30.620 --> 00:52:33.280 align:middle line:84%
And so, back to
the original idea,

00:52:33.280 --> 00:52:35.770 align:middle line:84%
we have to demonstrate that
in every area of our life.

00:52:35.770 --> 00:52:37.800 align:middle line:84%
And if you're changing
you, and I'm changing me,

00:52:37.800 --> 00:52:39.860 align:middle line:84%
and I'm giving up
resentment and hatred,

00:52:39.860 --> 00:52:41.890 align:middle line:84%
and you're giving up
jealousy and envy,

00:52:41.890 --> 00:52:44.510 align:middle line:84%
and it's no longer in
the fabric of your being,

00:52:44.510 --> 00:52:46.230 align:middle line:84%
and people are
noticing those changes,

00:52:46.230 --> 00:52:48.310 align:middle line:84%
imagine the effects
it has in the world.

00:52:48.310 --> 00:52:51.160 align:middle line:84%
We're not waiting for a
Gandhi or a Martin Luther King

00:52:51.160 --> 00:52:52.830 align:middle line:90%
or a Joan of Arc.

00:52:52.830 --> 00:52:55.260 align:middle line:84%
This is the time when you
and I and the simple person

00:52:55.260 --> 00:52:56.970 align:middle line:84%
has to be able to
demonstrate it.

00:52:56.970 --> 00:52:59.410 align:middle line:84%
And science is the language
to really demystify it.

00:52:59.410 --> 00:53:02.970 align:middle line:84%
And that's what unifies
the culture and tradition

00:53:02.970 --> 00:53:03.530 align:middle line:90%
and religion.

00:53:03.530 --> 00:53:05.696 align:middle line:84%
Because the moment you start
talking about tradition

00:53:05.696 --> 00:53:07.460 align:middle line:84%
or culture or
religion, you begin

00:53:07.460 --> 00:53:08.850 align:middle line:90%
to separate your audience.

00:53:08.850 --> 00:53:10.806 align:middle line:84%
Science has become the
contemporary language.

00:53:10.806 --> 00:53:11.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:53:11.680 --> 00:53:15.230 align:middle line:84%
And if you can take
just one minute or so

00:53:15.230 --> 00:53:19.820 align:middle line:84%
and address the-- and again,
I would recommend watching,

00:53:19.820 --> 00:53:22.240 align:middle line:84%
and I'll mention that again
later, our first interview.

00:53:22.240 --> 00:53:25.000 align:middle line:84%
You went into some great
depth on the subject

00:53:25.000 --> 00:53:27.890 align:middle line:84%
of how the brain is entrained,
how the cell memory is

00:53:27.890 --> 00:53:29.640 align:middle line:84%
entrained, when you're
getting your kicks,

00:53:29.640 --> 00:53:31.780 align:middle line:84%
you have to keep pushing
and pushing the envelope.

00:53:31.780 --> 00:53:33.020 align:middle line:90%
We didn't get to that today.

00:53:33.020 --> 00:53:34.740 align:middle line:84%
But we did talk
about it last time,

00:53:34.740 --> 00:53:36.460 align:middle line:90%
and video games and little kids.

00:53:36.460 --> 00:53:37.960 align:middle line:84%
What would you say
to moms and dads?

00:53:37.960 --> 00:53:39.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, listen,
I mean in my house

00:53:39.540 --> 00:53:41.500 align:middle line:84%
with my kids were growing
up, here's the rule,

00:53:41.500 --> 00:53:42.747 align:middle line:90%
we had five seconds.

00:53:42.747 --> 00:53:44.830 align:middle line:84%
If I asked you a question
and you couldn't respond

00:53:44.830 --> 00:53:46.740 align:middle line:84%
in five seconds, then
you were addicted.

00:53:46.740 --> 00:53:47.900 align:middle line:90%
Game over.

00:53:47.900 --> 00:53:49.564 align:middle line:84%
But when you're
killing somebody,

00:53:49.564 --> 00:53:51.730 align:middle line:84%
you're shooting somebody,
you're blowing somebody up

00:53:51.730 --> 00:53:54.250 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is, there's
a release of dopamine

00:53:54.250 --> 00:53:54.820 align:middle line:90%
in the brain.

00:53:54.820 --> 00:53:56.320 align:middle line:90%
It's a pleasure chemical.

00:53:56.320 --> 00:54:00.900 align:middle line:84%
And when you squirt out all that
chemistry and norepinephrine,

00:54:00.900 --> 00:54:03.100 align:middle line:84%
when you keep doing
it, the receptor sites

00:54:03.100 --> 00:54:05.890 align:middle line:84%
on the outside of the
cells become desensitized.

00:54:05.890 --> 00:54:08.560 align:middle line:84%
So the next time you play,
they need a little bit more

00:54:08.560 --> 00:54:09.910 align:middle line:90%
to turn them on.

00:54:09.910 --> 00:54:11.800 align:middle line:84%
And so, the pleasure
centers in the brain

00:54:11.800 --> 00:54:14.220 align:middle line:84%
start recalibrating
to a higher level.

00:54:14.220 --> 00:54:17.280 align:middle line:84%
And now, you're addicted,
because you cannot get the same

00:54:17.280 --> 00:54:19.380 align:middle line:90%
rush as you did the day before.

00:54:19.380 --> 00:54:21.442 align:middle line:90%
Now, think about this.

00:54:21.442 --> 00:54:25.230 align:middle line:84%
This is a tragedy because, in
the absence of that chemicals

00:54:25.230 --> 00:54:28.110 align:middle line:84%
rush, they can't find
pleasure in anything.

00:54:28.110 --> 00:54:30.845 align:middle line:84%
You say, go watch a sunset or
let's go see your grandmother

00:54:30.845 --> 00:54:32.990 align:middle line:84%
or let's go take
the dog for a walk.

00:54:32.990 --> 00:54:36.220 align:middle line:84%
Well, they just murdered
a whole civilization

00:54:36.220 --> 00:54:37.362 align:middle line:90%
in their video game.

00:54:37.362 --> 00:54:39.320 align:middle line:84%
They're not going to find
any pleasure in that.

00:54:39.320 --> 00:54:41.950 align:middle line:84%
Now, learning should be a
reward in and of itself.

00:54:41.950 --> 00:54:44.190 align:middle line:84%
And the children now can't
find pleasure in learning,

00:54:44.190 --> 00:54:46.630 align:middle line:84%
and they have to wake their
brain up just to turn it on.

00:54:46.630 --> 00:54:48.610 align:middle line:84%
They're going to act
out and get in trouble.

00:54:48.610 --> 00:54:50.630 align:middle line:84%
And we have a culture
now that's based on,

00:54:50.630 --> 00:54:53.462 align:middle line:84%
when they get older and
have problems in their life,

00:54:53.462 --> 00:54:55.170 align:middle line:84%
instead of facing off
with the problems--

